    <h2><a id="cite"></a>How to cite ValPaL database</h2>
        <p>The ValPaL online database is an edited database consisting of different languages which should be regarded as separate publications, like chapters of an edited volume. These datasets exemplified by <a href="/languages/icelandic">Icelandic</a> should be cited as follows:
        </p>
            
<pre>Barðdal, Jóhanna. 2013. Icelandic Valency Patterns.
In: Hartmann, Iren &amp; Haspelmath, Martin &amp; Taylor, Bradley (eds.) 2013.
Valency Patterns Leipzig online database
Leipzig: Max Planck Institute for Evolutionary Anthropology.
(Available online at http://valpal.info, Accessed on <%= Time.now.strftime("%Y-%m-%d") %>)</pre>
        
        <p>The complete work should be cited as follows: 
            <a rel="popover" class="info cursor-hand" style="text-decoration:none;cursor:pointer;" title="BibTeX" data-content="<span style='font-size:9pt;font-family:monospace;'>@book{valpal,<br />
